.TH _PRINTF 3 "APRIL 2026" "Hadeel & Ahaad" "Custom Printf Manual"
.SH NAME
_printf \- formatted output conversion
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"
.BI "int _printf(const char *" format ", ...);"
.SH DESCRIPTION
This function produces output according to a format string.
.SH FORMAT
.SS Conversion Specifiers
.TP
.B c, s, %
Handle characters, strings, and the percent sign.
.TP
.B d, i
Handle signed decimal integers.
.SH EXAMPLES
_printf("Hello %s\\n", "Hadeel");
_printf("Number: %d\\n", 2026);
.SH AUTHORS
Hadeel and Ahaad.
